  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Since 9<i>y</i> is a common factor of each term, the expression can be rewritten as 9<i>y</i>(<i>y</i><sup>10</sup> &minus; <i>y</i><sup>9</sup> + 9). Multiplying back: 9<i>y</i> &middot; <i>y</i><sup>10</sup> = 9<i>y</i><sup>11</sup>, 9<i>y</i> &middot; (&minus;<i>y</i><sup>9</sup>) = &minus;9<i>y</i><sup>10</sup>, and 9<i>y</i> &middot; 9 = 81<i>y</i>.</p><p>Choice B is incorrect because the exponents inside the parentheses are not reduced after factoring out <i>y</i>. Choice C results from using 8 instead of 9 as the numerical factor. Choice D incorrectly raises the constant 9 to powers instead of <i>y</i>.</p>",
